Important public interest meetings should not be held in Mombasa as participants sneak out to the beaches, but should be held in national parks with dangerous animal to keep participants in the meeting, NCIC chairman Francis ole Kaparo has said.He spoke yesterday in Mombasa during the Second Annual National Legislative Summit that brought together MCAs and senators from all counties.Kaparo said taxpayers&rsquo; money was spent on organising the forum, but the event has been poorly attended since Monday. Some leaders made technical appearances.Yesterday, the hall that usually hosts about 800 participants had just around 80 attendees. Some MCAs were seen shopping in the CBD.